@startuml
' Author: Nicholas Irvine  GitHub https://github.com/SaladStik  LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicholas-irvine-303ab5284/
title Orbit TLS at the Edge

' TLS lives in exactly one place, the nginx edge. Plain :80 is
' only there to bounce you up to :443. Internal services speak plain HTTP on
' the trusted network. They never deal with certificates.

actor Browser

rectangle "nginx (edge)" as nginx {
  component ":80\nHTTP" as p80
  component ":443\nHTTPS (TLS)" as p443
}

component "internal services\n(ui, auth, gateway, ...)" as internal

Browser --> p80 : http://localhost
p80 --> Browser : 301 -> https://localhost
Browser --> p443 : https://localhost\n(self-signed cert)

p443 --> internal : plain HTTP\n(trusted internal network)

note bottom of nginx : TLS terminates here. The cert is mounted, not baked in.
note right of internal : No certs inside. Plain HTTP on the private network.

@enduml
